YouTube mainly runs on Google’s own cloud ecosystem, not on third-party clouds.

1. Client Layer

Web App / Mobile App → Used to provide user interface for watching, uploading and interacting with videos → Used when applications must support multi-device access.

HTML5 Video Player → Used to stream videos directly in browser without plugins → Used when cross-platform video playback is required.

Google Front End (GFE) → Entry point server that receives user requests → Used when global applications need a secure edge entry layer.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. DNS + Routing Layer

Google DNS → Converts youtube.com into IP address → Used when applications need domain name resolution.

Anycast Routing → Routes users to nearest data center → Used when latency must be minimized globally.

Edge POP Servers → First contact servers near users → Used when reducing response delay is critical.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Load Balancing Layer

Maglev Load Balancer → Distributes traffic across backend servers → Used when handling millions of concurrent users.

Global Load Balancer → Routes traffic between regions → Used when multi-region failover is required.

Health Check Services → Detects failed servers → Used when high availability is needed.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. API Gateway Layer

API Gateway → Routes requests to backend services → Used when microservices must be centrally managed.

Authentication Service → Validates users → Used when login systems exist.

Rate Limiter → Prevents abuse → Used when APIs must prevent spam or attacks.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Microservices Layer

User Service → Manages profiles and subscriptions → Used when user management is required.

Video Metadata Service → Stores video info → Used when managing video data.

Comment Service → Handles comments → Used when social interaction features exist.

Search Service → Processes search queries → Used when applications require search functionality.

Recommendation Service → Suggests videos → Used when AI personalization is needed.
